## Research Cache TTLs

Every metric fetched in the research pipeline has a defined TTL. Do not cache metrics marked
"no cache", and do not extend TTLs without an ADR in `docs/DECISIONS.md`.

### TTL reference

| Metric | TTL | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| `market_cap` | 30 days | Slow-moving fundamental |
| `category` | 30 days | Producer / Developer / Explorer / Royalty — rarely changes |
| `jurisdiction_risk` | 30 days | Country-level rating, infrequent updates |
| `aisc` | 30 days | All-in sustaining cost from quarterly reports |
| `institutional_interest` | 30 days | 13F filings are quarterly |
| `upcoming_catalysts` | 30 days | Earnings dates, permit decisions — scheduled events |
| `short_term_returns` | 1 day | 3d / 7d / 14d rolling returns |
| `volume_spikes` | no cache | Intraday signal, always fetch live |
| `volatility` | no cache | Intraday signal, always fetch live |
| `metal_correlation` | no cache | Rolling divergence vs spot price |
| `news_sentiment` | no cache | News cycle moves fast |
| `social_sentiment` | no cache | Reddit / social moves fast |
| `analyst_sentiment` | no cache | Ratings can change without notice |
| `insider_trades` | no cache | Material non-public risk if stale |
| `option_flows` | no cache | Not yet implemented; cache TBD |

### Implementation rules

- Cache keys must include the ticker symbol and the metric name: `f"{ticker}:{metric}"`
- Store the `fetched_at` timestamp alongside every cached value
- On cache hit, compare `fetched_at + ttl` against `now()` before returning — do not trust DB-level expiry alone
- On cache miss, fetch, store, then return
- The `short_term_returns` cache must be invalidated if a corporate action (split, dividend) is detected
- Never cache a value that arrived with an error or empty response — re-fetch on next pipeline run
